        <p style="font: bold 15px/17px 'Times New Roman'; padding-left: 226px; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">VOTING INFORMATION</p>
        <p style="font: bold 15px/17px 'Times New Roman'; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">Quorum and Required Vote for the Proposal</p>
        <p style="font: 15px/17px 'Times New Roman'; text-align: justify; padding-right: 91px; margin-top: 11px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">Under the Master Trust Agreement of the Trust, a majority of the shares entitled to vote on a Proposal constitutes a quorum for the transaction of business with respect to that Proposal. According to the Master Trust Agreement, a majority of the shares voted at a meeting at which a quorum is present will decide any questions, and a plurality will elect a Trustee. In the event that a quorum is not present at the Meeting, or in the event that a quorum is present but sufficient votes to approve the Proposal or any other matter as may properly come before the Meeting are not received, the persons named as proxies may propose one or more adjournments of the Meeting to permit further solicitation of proxies with respect to the Proposal.</p>
        <p style="font: 15px/17px 'Times New Roman'; text-align: justify; padding-right: 96px; margin-top: 9px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">In determining whether to adjourn the Special Meeting, the following factors may be considered: the nature of the Proposal that is the subject of the Special Meeting, the percentage of votes actually cast, the percentage of negative votes actually cast, the nature of any further solicitation and the additional information, if any, to be provided to shareholders with respect to the reasons for the solicitation. Any adjournment will require the affirmative vote of a majority of those shares represented at the virtual Meeting or by proxy. The persons named as proxies will vote in favor of such adjournment those shares that they are entitled to vote and that have been voted in favor of such Proposal.</p>
        <p style="font: 15px/17px 'Times New Roman'; text-align: justify; padding-right: 96px; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">A Shareholder vote may be taken on the Proposal or on any other matter that may properly come before the Meeting prior to any adjournment if sufficient votes have been received and it is otherwise appropriate. For purposes of determining the presence of a quorum for transacting business at the Meeting, abstentions and broker "non-votes" (that is, proxies from brokers or Nominees indicating that these persons have not received instructions from the beneficial owner or other persons entitled to vote shares on a particular matter with respect to which the brokers or nominees do not have discretionary power), if any, will be treated as shares that are present but which have not been voted. An affirmative vote of a plurality of the shares present or represented by proxy for all Funds that compose the Trust voting as a single class is required to elect the Nominees for election as Trustees.</p>
        <p style="font: bold 15px/17px 'Times New Roman'; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">Abstentions and Broker Non-Votes</p>
        <p style="font: 15px/17px 'Times New Roman'; margin: 0px; text-align: justify; padding-right: 96px; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">Abstentions and broker "non-votes" will be counted for purposes of determining whether a quorum is present at the Special Meeting.</p>
        <p style="font: bold 15px/17px 'Times New Roman'; margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">Voting</p>
        <p style="font: 14px/16px 'Times New Roman'; margin: 0px; text-align: justify; padding-right: 91px; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">Shares represented by duly executed proxies will be voted at the Meeting in accordance with the instructions given. <font style="font: bold 14px/17px 'Times New Roman'; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">However, if no instructions are specified on the proxy with respect to the Proposal(s), shares will be voted FOR the approval of the Proposal(s) and in accordance with the judgment of the persons</font></p>
        <p style="font: 16px/19px 'Times New Roman'; padding-left: 304px; margin-top: 5px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">13</p>
        </div>
        <p style="page-break-before: always;">&#160;</p>
        <div style="margin: 104px 0px 102px 96px; padding: 0px; width: 720px; overflow: hidden; position: relative;">
        <p style="font: 14px/16px 'Times New Roman'; margin: 0px; text-align: justify; padding-right: 91px; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;"><font style="font: bold 14px/17px 'Times New Roman'; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">appointed as proxies upon any other matter that may properly come before the Meeting. </font>If you wish to participate in the Meeting, you may submit the proxy card included with this Proxy Statement or attend via the live webcast to be held at <font style="font: 14px/16px 'Times New Roman'; color: #0000ff; text-decoration: underline; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">https://viewproxy.com/MorganStanleyPathwayFunds/broadridgevsm/</font>&#160;. &#160;Your vote is important no matter how many shares you own. You can vote easily and quickly by telephone, Internet, mail or at the Meeting. Should you require additional information regarding the proxy or replacement proxy cards, you may contact the Trust at 1-800-869-3326.</p>
        <p style="font: bold 15px/17px 'Times New Roman'; margin-top: 32px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">Revocation</p>
        <p style="font: 15px/17px 'Times New Roman'; text-align: justify; padding-right: 96px; margin-top: 7px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">A shareholder may revoke a previously submitted proxy at any time prior to the Meeting by (i) a written revocation, which must be signed and include the shareholder's name and account number, received by the Secretary of the Trust at 2000 Westchester Avenue, Purchase, New York 10577; (ii) properly executing a later-dated proxy; or (iii) attending the Meeting and voting via the live webcast.</p>
        <p style="font: bold 15px/17px 'Times New Roman'; padding-left: 229px; margin-top: 33px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">OTHER INFORMATION</p>
        <p style="font: bold 15px/17px 'Times New Roman'; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">Solicitation of Proxies, Payment of Expenses</p>
        <p style="font: 15px/17px 'Times New Roman'; text-align: justify; padding-right: 96px; margin-top: 11px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">The solicitation of proxies is being made on behalf of the Board, on behalf of the Funds. The Funds have retained Broadridge Financial Solutions, Inc. (the "Proxy Solicitor") to aid in the solicitation. The costs of retaining the Proxy Solicitor and other expenses incurred in connection with the solicitation of proxies will be paid by the Funds. The anticipated cost associated with the solicitation of proxies by the Proxy Solicitor is expected to be nominal, because of the voting structure of the Funds' shareholders. If necessary, proxies may be solicited by mail, electronically, by telephone, fax, in person or by other means, and representatives of the Proxy Solicitor, the Trust, CGAS, the Administrator and MSWM may participate in the solicitation of proxies.</p>
        <p style="font: 15px/17px 'Times New Roman'; text-align: justify; padding-right: 96px; margin-top: 9px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">The Funds will pay all expenses related to conducting this solicitation of proxies, including, but not limited to, preparation, printing and mailing of this Proxy Statement and its enclosures, legal fees, and solicitation costs. The Trust estimates these costs to be approximately $550,000. The payment of such fees will be considered an extraordinary expense for the Funds and, therefore, will not be subject to any expense limitation or reimbursement agreement in effect for the Funds.</p>
        <p style="font: bold 15px/17px 'Times New Roman'; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">Shareholders Sharing the Same Address</p>
        <p style="font: 15px/17px 'Times New Roman'; margin: 0px; text-align: justify; padding-right: 96px; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">If two or more shareholders share the same address, only one copy of this Proxy Statement may be delivered to that address, unless the Trust has received contrary instructions from one or more of the shareholders at that shared address. Upon written or oral request, the Trust will deliver promptly a separate copy of this Proxy Statement to a shareholder at a shared address. Please note that each shareholder will receive a separate proxy card, regardless of whether he or she resides at a shared address. Please call 1-800-869-3326 or forward a written request to the Trust at 2000 Westchester Avenue, Purchase, New York 10577, if you would like to: (1) receive a separate copy of this Proxy Statement; (2) receive your annual reports, semi- annual reports or proxy statements separately in the future; or (3) request delivery of a single copy of annual reports, semi-annual reports or proxy statements if you are currently receiving multiple copies at a shared address.</p>
        <p style="font: bold 15px/17px 'Times New Roman'; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">Shareholder Proposals</p>
        <p style="font: 15px/17px 'Times New Roman'; margin: 0px; text-align: justify; padding-right: 96px; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">The Trust does not hold Shareholder meetings annually. Shareholders wishing to submit proposals for consideration for inclusion in a proxy statement for the next Shareholder meeting should send their written proposals to Morgan Stanley Pathway Funds, 2000 Westchester Avenue, Purchase, New York 10577, c/o the Trust's Secretary. The Board of Trustees will consider whether any such proposal should be submitted</p>
        <p style="font: 16px/19px 'Times New Roman'; margin: 0px; padding-left: 304px; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">14</p>
        </div>
        <p style="page-break-before: always;">&#160;</p>
        <div style="margin: 104px 0px 102px 96px; padding: 0px; width: 720px; overflow: hidden; position: relative;">
        <p style="font: 15px/17px 'Times New Roman'; margin: 0px; text-align: justify; padding-right: 97px; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">to a shareholder vote in light of applicable rules and interpretations promulgated by the SEC; but a shareholder's timely submission of a proposal will not automatically confer a right to have that proposal presented for a vote at the Meeting.</p>
        <p style="font: bold 15px/17px 'Times New Roman'; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">Beneficial Ownership of Shares and Security Ownership of Management</p>
        <p style="font: 15px/17px 'Times New Roman'; text-align: justify; padding-right: 96px; margin-top: 11px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">As of the Record Date, no persons were record owners or, to the knowledge of the Funds, were beneficial owners of 5% or more of the Funds' outstanding shares.</p>
        <p style="font: bold 15px/17px 'Times New Roman'; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">Other Business</p>
        <p style="font: 15px/17px 'Times New Roman'; text-align: justify; padding-right: 96px; margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">The Board does not intend to present any other business at the Meeting. If any other matter may properly come before the Meeting, or any adjournment(s) thereof, the persons named in the accompanying proxy card intend to vote, act, or consent thereunder in accordance with their best judgment at that time with respect to such matters unless such proxy contains specific restrictions to the contrary.</p>
        <p style="font: bold 15px/17px 'Times New Roman'; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">Annual Report to Shareholders</p>
        <p style="font: 15px/17px 'Times New Roman'; margin: 0px; text-align: justify; padding-right: 96px; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">For a free copy of the Trust's most recent annual report and most recent semi-annual report preceding the annual report, shareholders of the Funds may call your financial intermediary (such as a financial advisor) or, if you are a direct investor, 1-800-869-3326 or write to the Funds at 2000 Westchester Avenue, Purchase, New York 10577.</p>
        <p style="font: bold 15px/17px 'Times New Roman'; padding-left: 107px; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">THE BOARD, INCLUDING THE INDEPENDENT TRUSTEES,</p>
        <p style="font: bold 15px/17px 'Times New Roman'; margin: 0px; padding-left: 67px; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">UNANIMOUSLY RECOMMENDS THAT SHAREHOLDERS VOTE "FOR"</p>
        <p style="font: bold 15px/17px 'Times New Roman'; margin: 0px; padding-left: 253px; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">THE PROPOSAL.</p>
        <p style="font: bold 15px/17px 'Times New Roman'; margin-top: 35px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">PROMPT EXECUTION AND RETURN OF THE ENCLOSED PROXY CARD IS REQUESTED.</p>
        <p style="font: bold 15px/17px 'Times New Roman'; margin: 0px; padding-right: 101px; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;"><font style="font: bold 15px/17px 'Times New Roman'; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">A</font><font style="font: bold 15px/17px 'Times New Roman'; margin-left: 3px; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">SELF-ADDRESSED,</font> POSTAGE-PAID ENVELOPE IS ENCLOSED FOR YOUR CONVENIENCE. YOU MAY ALSO VOTE BY TELEPHONE OR ON THE INTERNET. ANY UNMARKED PROXIES WITHOUT INSTRUCTIONS TO THE CONTRARY WILL BE VOTED IN FAVOR OF APPROVAL OF THE PROPOSAL.</p>
        <p style="font: 16px/19px 'Times New Roman'; padding-left: 304px; margin-top: 329px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;">15</p>
        </div>
